            <div facs="ht:chi.12945678&amp;view=1up&amp;seq=1023" type="entry">
                <p><label type="entry">ZEBID</label>, a city of Arabia, once the capital of Yemen;
                    but its port having fallen into a state of decay, the principal city of the
                    province is now Mocha. The old mosques and minarets still give to the place a
                    magnificent appearance from a distance, and it is still distinguished by an
                    academy, much resorted to by the youth of Yemen. But it is gradually falling
                    into ruins, so that it has become an employment for the people to carry off the
                    stones, which are sold to be elsewhere applied to the purposes of building.
                    Zebid is 52 miles north of Mocha.</p>
            </div>
